'''Level 632''' is the 633<sup><u>rd</u></sup> level of the backrooms.

== Description ==
'''Level 632''' has the appearance of an abandoned facility. '''Level 632''' consists of pipes, concrete walls, and moss growth. Most rooms are pitch black, with shattered glass on the floor and broken lighting. Some places with lighting are hard to come by. There's a mild breeze that blows across the entire level.

Hallways are one of the most common areas of the level and are typically dark. They connect to other areas of the level. Lights are found uncommonly in the hallways and contain pipes and some moss. [[Object 10|Backshrooms]] and moss are also very plentiful in hallways. Entities are quite common in the hallways, roaming around.

The bathrooms are uncommon to find; they have some stalls. The toilets inside the stalls are full of liquid pain and are unable to flush, and the sink uses liquid pain instead of water; the mirrors of the sink are typically shattered everywhere. The bathrooms also produce a foul smell inside from the liquid pain and have a decent chance of having entities. Sometimes, it has vents which lead to the electrical rooms or, rarely, the water treatment zone. No food can be spotted in the bathrooms, only jars of liquid pain.

The Water Treatment Zone is located outside the facility. It is a wasteland full of cooling towers, cooling units, and storage tanks containing radioactive water with a horrible odor. The grass of the treatment zone is dead and withered, and the dead trees are littered across the plant. This area is extremely high in radiation from the radioactive water. It is advised to stay inside the facility, as short-term presence in the area will have irreversible damage to tissue and DNA. 

The electrical room has pipes, generators, a concrete floor, and other electrical components. There are also many coins on the floor of the room, which are only used for the vending machines in the breakroom. The electric wires are a hazard in the room; the area powers the parts of the facility and the water treatment facility. The generators that power the facility leak oil and smoke. At any point, the generators make a short circuit and explode. The pipes circulate a mysterious coolant in the room, which can also be found outside of the electrical room and in the hallways. Also, workers are commonly found in the electrical room, fixing the generators and pipes throughout. They are less aggressive in the room compared to anywhere else. It is theorized by many that the reason is that they are busy fixing the electrical components. 

The breakroom is at the center of the level and has working lights, marble flooring, and concrete walls. It also has an abundance of food and drinks, especially almond water, which all come from vending machines. The room also has sofas and tables, and a cool air conditioner on the ceiling. The vending machines only accept a certain coin that is only found in the electrical rooms. The breakroom is the safest part of the level since fewer entities are in the breakroom; radiation is barely a threat in the break room, as most of it hasn't reached this area yet. The workers also come to this area to rest; they aren't hostile or have a drive to experiment on anybody, typically thought to be resting by wanderers.

The test chambers have lights, shattered marble flooring, and concrete walls. The area has tables loosely littered around the rooms, which contain notes about an experiment and the drawing of the outcome. There are also glass flasks that contain dangerous chemical compounds and elements such as hydrochloric acid, chlorine, etc. The workers also experiment on wanderers inside the test chambers, injecting them with chemicals and bio weapons, and eventually subduing them by injecting a radioactive compound into their bloodstream. The test chamber is the most unsafe part of the level from the abundance of mutants, due to the high amount of radioactivity in the area, and the workers experimenting on them.

=== Security Breach ===
A security breach is an event that happens uncommonly at this level. When a security breach occurs, a loud alarm sounds at the level, and the level releases a type of mustard gas, intended to stop the entities from breaching the facility. Entities outside of the level, which are: [[Entity 6|Dullers]], [[Entity 5|Clumps]], [[Entity 3|Smilers]], [[Entity 10|Skin Stealers]], and many more, will attempt to break into the facility. They start to come from the water treatment plant and try to find and kill any nearby wanderers; it is unknown why they are more hostile and try to attack any wanderers. The security breach event lasts for about 30 minutes to an hour.

=== Radiation ===
Ionizing radiation is a prevalent threat in all parts in the level. Radiation mutates wanderers or infects them with radiation poisoning; long-term presence in it will turn wanderers into mutants, because it makes them susceptible to the Mutant disease. It can also have long term damage such as hormone disruptions and cancer. Radiation is most common at the Test Chambers and the Water Treatment Zone. It is believed that before a reactor exploded in the test chambers, infecting most of the level with radiation. Radiation at a certain level can weaken a wanderer's cells to the point that the Mutant disease can enter the wanderer's body and eventually control their mind. 

=== Discovery & Origin of Level 632 ===

The level was first found by an M.E.G. group, who are Sammy Si, Donald Richardson, Marcus Uy, and Charie Corro, who were all attempting to reach [[Level 4]]. In the beginning, threats were not present. Aside from the security breaches, the level was a moderately safe area. The workers were all working on the test chambers, which hold the reactor, but they failed to stabilize it, so it exploded throughout the entire level. The loss of the reactor shut down most of the lights in the level. A radioactive mist formed from the test chambers, the radioactivity spread throughout all of the level, especially the water treatment zone. Making the level a radioactive wasteland, by the time the reactor exploded, the workers started experimenting on other wanderers who came to the level.

== Entities ==

=== Mutant ===
Mutants are abundant in the level and reside in every part of the level. They appear to be humans who are mutilated. The mutant's skin has mutated with cracks all over; this is also where they produce spores. Their fingernails are sharp and long; they also have exceptional hearing and heightened senses compared to a normal wanderer. Due to the level being mostly dark, mutants use echolocation to traverse the level. When they die, their bodies explode, spreading the virus. These entities aren't naturally aggressive, only hunting for food and sustenance; their true danger is their ability to spread its spores. The spores they emit is more dangerous than usual, as they can emit radiation; it also takes significantly less days to enter and control the host. 

==== Effects of the Mutant Disease to Wanderers ====
The Mutant virus can't infect the wanderer through their mouth or eyes; they need radiation damage to living cells and tissue in the body so the virus can enter the body, however the mutants production of spores are much more efficient in infiltrating one and infecting them. An early effect of the virus on wanderers is that they become irrational and tend not follow with other wanderers. A later effect of the virus is that it usually controls the brain, eventually turning wanderers into mutants; this effect comes after 10 up to 14 days of having the disease. Once they transform into a mutant, mercy killing is the best option.

==== Workers ====
Workers are uncommon at this level. Workers resemble humans wearing work clothes and have white, glowing eyes. The worker's skin is pale and dry. Workers are commonly not hostile unless provoked, but some workers put wanderers in a test chamber to turn them into mutants as an "experiment". They are also immune to radiation, as they have cells that repair almost immediately. Workers are the first entities found in the level; the workers used to work in the reactor core before it exploded. It is unknown why and how the reactor was in the test chambers. 

== Colonies & Outposts ==

=== The Resters ===

* Friendly and willing to help others.
* The Rester's outpost is in the breakroom.
* There are six members in the group.
* Heavily armed.

== Entrances & Exits ==

=== Entrances ===

* Touching a paper and saying help is wanted will send you to this level.
* In [[Level 3]] there is a door labeled "factory sector" when opened, leads to this level.
* No clipping in a barrel of liquid pain has a chance to send you to this level.
* In [[Level 289]] opening  and going inside trapdoor labeled "STAFF ONLY, NO ENTRY NO MATTER WHAT CAUSE" will lead you here.

=== Exits ===

* Escaping the water treatment zone to the forest brings you to [[Level 630]]. 
* Jumping into the radioactive water in a security breach event has a small chance to lead to [[Level 30]].
* Seeing a yellowish door and opening it will send you to [[Level 0]], however it is rare to find one.
* No clipping in the test chambers have a possibility to bring you to [[Level 153]].
* Noclipping inside the water treatment facility while it's snowing leads to [[Level 633]].
* Coming across an exit door will lead you to [[Level 289]].

